provider: github
owner: Louis-7
repo: deskopilot

# To enable auto-update testing in `npm run dev`:
#   1. cp dev-app-update.yml.example dev-app-update.yml
#   2. Lower the version in package.json (e.g. 0.0.1-alpha.0) so a published
#      release on GitHub appears as "newer".
#   3. Ensure the target release is *published* (not draft) on GitHub.
#   4. Run `npm run dev` — the tray "Check for Updates…" item will hit the
#      real GitHub feed and show the update dialog.
#
# Note: in dev mode, downloads land in app.getPath('userData')/__update__
# and `quitAndInstall()` will fail (no installer to launch). Use a packaged
# build to validate the install step end-to-end.
